review_blob: Couldnt decipher any certain aroma. Reddish brown appearance. Smoothe, but strong, ale-ish flavor on the back of the tongue. Good beer. Will sneak up on you with high etoh %.
Wish it was available all year. Rye/piney scent, hoppy/citrus flavor.  Solid beer.

As far as sour beers go, this may be my favorite. Subtle sweetness followed by the perfect amount of sour. Found that it was more enjoyable out of the 1pint, 9.4oz bottle than out of the 4pack of smaller bottles.
Smoothe but somewhat crisp subtle cocoa flavor. Chocolate tootsie pop scent. Good autumn beer.
